children: “Pick Up the Phone” details Travis, Thug and Quavo’s unfortunate situation. While they all want to be faithful and stay committed to this girl, she won’t show her love in return, refusing to pick up the phone—even while she’s not busy.
“Pick Up the Phone” is a bonus track off Young Thug’s mixtape,
Jeffery
, as well as the 11th track off  Travis Scott’s
Birds In The Trap Sing McKnight
This song was originally a collaboration between Young Thug and Quavo, with
Starrah singing the hook
. Travis was in the studio when Young Thug recorded the song, and he wrote the bridge for Young Thug (early versions of this song exist where Travis sang the bridge instead).

Travis then began playing his altered version at clubs and called it his own single without notifying Young Thug. Travis teased the song for months before he finally leaked it on his own SoundCloud because the labels would not release it. An agreement was made that the song would be released on iTunes later that day as a joint single between Thug and Travis.
“Pick Up the Phone” and
“goosebumps”
are
certified platinum
by the RIAA as of January 11, 2017.
